`crates/steno/src/expand/` implements the multi-pass expansion pipeline that turns a parsed `Entry` AST into `TypedEntry` records consumed by both steno's translation renderer and its doc renderer. Depending on this module gets you one entry point, `expand_dict(entries, generic_arg_strokes) -> Result<Vec<TypedEntry>, ExpandError>`; everything else (the five-pass internal structure) is an implementation detail behind that call.

The pipeline is strictly staged and order-dependent, and that order lives only in `mod.rs`'s `expand_dict`: `build_type_set` (types.rs) first partitions `@type`-flagged entries into `types`/`arity0` pools (optionally filtered by `generic_arg_strokes`), then each remaining `Entry` goes through Pass A (`counts.rs::expand_counts`, count/repeat resolution, producing `ExpandedEntry`) and Pass B (`append.rs::expand_types_one`, `%t`-slot resolution using `fill.rs`'s `Filling` enumeration and `types.rs`'s `TypeDef`/`TypeOptions`, producing `TypedEntry`). Only once every entry in the batch is typed do the two whole-batch corrections run: `family.rs::fix_family_terminals` (clears `terminal` on stroke-prefix "family roots") and `lineflag.rs::expand_line_flag` (adds one-liner variants via a `U`-flagged first stroke). Running family/lineflag per-entry instead of over the full vector silently breaks their cross-entry logic — this is the one invariant a cross-file change must preserve.

Two staging structs, both defined in `mod.rs`, are the coupling surface between passes: `ExpandedEntry` (Pass A output, count-resolved template, no `Repeat`/`Dcount`/`Computed` chunks left, but `%t`/`%b`/braces/landings still unresolved) and `TypedEntry` (Pass B output, adds `terminal`/`one_liner` flags that downstream renderers branch on). `append.rs` and `fill.rs` are tightly coupled: `Filling`'s shape and `fillings()`'s enumeration order in fill.rs directly determine what `append.rs`'s `appended`/`expand_fused`/`rec_multi` produce, and `fill.rs`'s free-type `Landing`-numbering convention must match whatever the chunk/template renderer expects. `types.rs` enforces that `@type` templates contain only `Lit`/`TypeSlot` chunks — no other pass may rely on richer `@type` syntax. `fill.rs` is private to the module (no `pub use`), reachable only through `append.rs` and `types.rs`.

Each submodule's role: `counts.rs` is Pass A; `types.rs` builds the append-set model consumed by `fill.rs`/`append.rs`; `fill.rs` enumerates fill chains (private helper); `append.rs` is Pass B; `family.rs` and `lineflag.rs` are the two post-typing whole-batch corrections, in that order.